 Chart about Governing Export and Import of Commodities 1.The Electronic Licensing System for Export/Import of Commodities provides services about (1)applications for Import/Export Permits, (2)application procedures for exportation of CD manufacturing machinery, (3)reference documents for imports of Chapter 94 Bedding, (4)applications for import approval for masks, etc. For more information, please clicks on the regulations and the options. 2. Import and Export Regulations Query 3. Importation of Mainland China products Query Apply 01 Log in with the &ldquo;MOEA Certification Authority IC Card&rdquo; or user account. 01 Log in 02 Select application type: I/p, E/p, Masks. etc. 02 Type of application 03 Fill out the form and supplementary doc. 03 Application form 04 Check results: (1) Approved , (2) Denied. 04 Review 05 Print out approval doc. 05 Download and print ::: Sitemap Expanded Sourcing from Taiwan Digital Trade Feature Service Overseas Services Trade Financing Trade Relations Multilateral Trade Bilateral Trade FTAs Trade Remedy Cases New Southbound MICE Industry MICE Advantages MICE Facilities Trade Law & Administration Trade Law Registration of Exporters and Importers Import & Export Administration CITES Certificates of Origin Export Control(SHTC) Information & Trade Stats Forecast Trade Statistics About Us Organization Location & Map Introduction Director General and Deputy Directors General Contact Us Overseas Offices News & Press Releases News Events Announcement TITA - 1 Hu Kou Street, Zhongzheng Dist., Taipei, 100057, Taiwan, R.O.C. 886-2-23510271 Toll-Free Service Hotline：0800-002-571 886-2-23517080,23513603 Kaoshsiung Office - 2F, No. 103, Zhongzheng 4th Road, Qianjin Dist., Kaohsiung, 80147, Taiwan, R.O.C. 886-7-2711171 Toll-Free Service Hotline：0800-668-682 886-7-2811396 Office Hours：AM 8:30 ~ PM 12:30; PM 13:30 ~ PM 17:30 Service Hours：AM 9:00 ~ PM 17:00 Best Browse in 1600 x 900 pixel with Internet Explorer 10.0 or above Visitor： 9084158 Update Da